issue.title: streamsstats evalution backwards in time
issue.body:
Hi Douglas
Because streamstats seems to evaluate results backwards in time (in the order they are delivered, lot of discussion about this on Splunk Answers) the unique vector is actually increased on the last occurrence of a new value not on the first one in time. Using "reverse" will put the whole thing in right order (hopefully without perfomance impact).

issue.title: Timeformat for period
issue.body:
Hi Douglas
Great little app, I will be happy to test it soon with real life data. Meanwhile I had a quick look into your search. Seems to me that there's a bit of confusion about time format (24h vs am/pm) at 
eval period=case(date_hour<5, 0, date_hour<8, 1, date_hour<12, 2, date_hour<5, 3, date_hour<8, 4, date_hour<24, 5) 
Shouldn't it be instead
eval period=case(date_hour<5, 0, date_hour<8, 1, date_hour<12, 2, date_hour<17, 3, date_hour<20, 4, date_hour<24, 5)

issue.title: Inability to use set operations
issue.body: The inability to apply set operations on values of fields means that this correlation search isn't nearly as powerful as it could be. See here for more information: http://answers.splunk.com/answers/258504/how-to-count-the-the-number-of-elements-in-a-field.html

issue.title: Consolidate eventstats into one subsearch in a foreach command
issue.body:
The search has 5 similar eventstats commands. We should be able to consolidate those into one subsearch using the foreach command as seen below, however it fails with the error: "Error in 'foreach' command: Search pipeline may not contain non-streaming commands".

... | foreach autonomous_system period date_wday app dest [eventstats count as <<FIELD>>_count by user, <<FIELD>>]

issue.title: Cannot be used to detect historical compromise
issue.body: It would be good if the correlation search could be run manually over historical events to detect existing compromised accounts, however to the best of my knowledge this isn't possible because the streamstats command can't be reversed (in real-time searches).
